## General Idea


Study the interplay of different types of exchanges between heavy-light mesons (B meson) meditated by t(u)-channel one-boson exchanges and s-channel exchanges through quark-model quarkonium states

---

.align{start}
	- full interaction potential $ V = V_{\text{OME}} + V_{\text{QM}} $
	  - parameters in $ V_{\text{OME}} $ are fixed and well known
	  - parameters in $ V_{\text{QM}} $ are fitted from lattice result of Born-Oppenheimer potential [Phys. Lett. B **793**, 493 (2019)](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.physletb.2019.05.018), [Phys. Lett. B **854**, 138754 (2024)](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.physletb.2024.138754)
	- quantum number for the $ X_b $ 
	  $ J^{PC} = 1^{++} $
	  - heavy quark spin symmetry(HQSS) $ S_{b\bar{b}}^{\text{fin}} = S_{b\bar{b}}^{\text{in}} = 1^{++} $
	  - ground state of BO potential $ j_l^{PC} = 0^{++}, L_{b\bar{b}}^{\text{fin}} = 1 $
	  - first excited state $ L_{b\bar{b}}^{\text{fin}} = 0, j_l^{PC} = 1^{--} $
	- exact isospin symmetry and SU(3) violation by strange quark mass
	  - two coupled channels $ \ket{B \bar{B}^*} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}(\ket{B_u\bar{B}_u^*} + \ket{B_d\bar{B}_d^*}),\hspace{11pt}\ket{B_s\bar{B}_s^*} $

$$$
V = 
\begin{pmatrix}
V(B\bar{B}^* \to B\bar{B}^*) & V(B\bar{B}^*\to B_s\bar{B}^*_s)\\
V(B_s\bar{B}^*_s \to B\bar{B}^*) & V(B_s\bar{B}_s^* \to B_s\bar{B}_s^*)
\end{pmatrix}
$$$

