## One Meson Exchange Interaction
---

$$$
\mathcal{L}_{\Phi}=\frac{g_{\scriptscriptstyle b}}4\text{Tr}\left(\vec{\sigma}\cdot\vec{u}_{ab}\bar{H}_b\bar{H}_a^{\dagger}\right)+\text{h.c.}\\
H_a = P_a + V_a^i\sigma^i,\hspace{11pt}\bar{H}_a = \bar{P}_a + \bar{V}_a^i\sigma^i
$$$


Lagrangian for $ \phi $-field coupling to pair of heavy-light mesons

$ \mathcal{L}_\phi = \frac{g_b}{2f_\pi}(V_a^{i\dagger}P_b + P_a^\dagger V_b^i + \bar{P}_a^\dagger \bar{V}_b^i + \bar{V}_a^{\dagger i}\bar{P}_b)\partial^i\phi_{ab} $

$ g_b \approx 0.57 , \hspace{11pt} f_\pi = 92.2 \text{MeV},\hspace{11pt} P_a = \{B^+, B^0, B_s\}, \hspace{11pt} V_a = \{B^{*+}, B^{*0}, B^*_s\} $

Time-Ordered Perturbation Theory(TOPT)

$ V_{\text{OME}}(p, p', m_G) = \frac{g_b^2}{24f_\pi^2}\int_{-1}^1 dx \frac{2pp'x - p^2 - p'^2}{2E_G(q)}\left[\frac{1}{E_G(q) + E_{1'}(p') + E_2(p) - M} + \frac{1}{E_G(q) + E_1(p) + E_{2'}(p') - M}\right] $

$ M $ is the energy

$ E_i(p) = m_i + \frac{p^2}{2m_i},\hspace{11pt} E_G = \sqrt{q^2 + m_G^2} $

<<<

## Quark Model States Exchange
---
Hamiltonian and Cornell potential
$$$
H_0 = -\frac{1}{2\mu}\nabla^2 + V(r)\\
V(r) = V_0 + \sigma r + \frac{\gamma}{r}
$$$

$ \sqrt{\sigma} = 445(3)_{\text{stat}}(6)_{\text{sys}}\text{MeV},\hspace{11pt}\gamma=-0.434(11) $

Rayleigh-Ritz principle, expand wavefuction using Gaussian basis [Prog. Part. Nucl. Phys. **51**, 223 (2003)](https://doi.org/10.1016/S0146-6410(03)90015-9)

$$$
\psi_n(\bm{r}) = \sum_{k = 1}^{k_{\text{max}}}c_{kl}\phi_{klm}(\bm{r}) = Y_{lm}(\hat{\bm{r}})\sum_{k = 0}^{k_{\text{max}}}c_{kl}\phi_{kl}(r)\\
\phi_{klm}(\bm{r}) = \phi_{kl}(r)Y_{lm}(\hat{\bm{r}}),\hspace{11pt}\phi_{kl}(r) = N_{kl}r^le^{-\nu_k r^2},\hspace{11pt}N_{kl} = \sqrt{\frac{2^{l+2}(2\nu_k)^{l+\frac{3}{2}}}{\sqrt{\pi}(2l+1)!!}}
$$$

Schrödinger equation becomes an eigenvalue problem

$ \sum_{k' = 1}^{k_{\text{max}}} = [H_{0kk'} - E\delta_{kk'}]c_{k'l} = 0 $

<<<

wavefuction as superposition of quark-model states and molecular states

$$$
\ket{\Psi} = 
\begin{pmatrix}
\lambda_n\ket{\psi_n}\\
\chi(\bm{p})\ket{M_1M_2}
\end{pmatrix},
\hspace{11pt}\mathcal{H} = 
\begin{pmatrix}
H_0 & \hat{g}\\
\hat{g} & V_l
\end{pmatrix}
$$$

Schrödinger equation for such a system

$$$
\mathcal{H} \ket{\Psi} = E\ket{\Psi},\hspace{15pt}
\begin{cases}
\lambda_n E_n + \int\frac{dp^3}{(2\pi)^3}\chi(\bm{p})\braket{\psi_n|\hat{g}|M_1M_2} = \lambda_n E\\
\sum_n\lambda_n\hat{g}\ket{\psi_n} + V_l\ket{M_1M_2} = E\ket{M_1M_2}
\end{cases}
$$$

$ \braket{\psi_n|\hat{g}|M_1M_2} \approx g\psi^*_n(\bm{p}) $

$ V_{\text{QM}}^{\alpha\beta}(\bm{p}, \bm{p}') = g^{\alpha}g^{\beta}\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{\psi_n(\bm{p})\psi_n^*(\bm{p}')}{E - E_n} $

<<<

## Lippmann-Schwinger Equation
---
The coupled channel Lippmann-Schwinger equation reads

$ T^{\alpha\beta}(E,\bm{p}, \bm{p}') = V^{\alpha\beta}(E, \bm{p}, \bm{p}') - \sum_\gamma\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}V^{\alpha\gamma}(E, \bm{p}, \bm{k})G_\gamma(E, \bm{k})T^{\gamma\beta}(E, \bm{k}, \bm{p}') $

$ G_\gamma(E, \bm{k}) = \frac{1}{k^2/(2\mu_\gamma) + \Delta_\gamma - E - i\epsilon} $

the integral equation is then discretized using Gauss-Legendre quadrature and becomes a matrix equation

$ \int_0^\Lambda dkf(k) \to \sum_n\tilde{\omega}_nf(k_n) $

$$$
T = V - VGT\\
T = [I + VG]^{-1}V
$$$

$ \text{pole}\{T\} = \text{root}\{\text{det}[I+VG]\} $

